solution: ```class Solution {
    public long findMaximumNumber(long k, int x) {
        long left = 1, right = 1L << 60;
        while (left < right) {
            long mid = left + (right - left + 1) / 2;
            if (accumulatedPrice(mid, x) <= k) {
                left = mid;
            } else {
                right = mid - 1;
            }
        }
        return left;
    }

    private long accumulatedPrice(long num, int x) {
        long total = 0;
        for (int p = x; p <= 60; p += x) {
            long full = (1L << p);
            long half = full >> 1;
            long cycles = (num + 1) / full;
            long rem = (num + 1) % full;
            total += cycles * half;
            if (rem > half) total += rem - half;
        }
        return total;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log² N) where N is the answer (binary search over 60-bit range, each check O(60/x))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Binary search the largest num whose accumulated price ≤ k. Accumulated price is computed by counting set bits at positions x,2x,… in 1..num using digit DP-like bit counting per bit position.

